  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>A <code>budget</code> is a plan that shows how much money you have and how you will spend it. For example, if you have $100, your <code>budget</code> will show what you will buy with that money and how much each thing costs.</p>\n<p><code>Budget allocation</code> means deciding how to divide and use the money in your <code>budget</code>. For example, if you have $100 and you decide to spend $50 on food and $50 on clothes, that is your <code>budget allocation</code>. It means choosing how to use your money for different things.</p>\n<p>Listen to Maria and fill in the blanks.</p>\n</section>",
